Jim Justice and his dog. Senator Justice (R) is the one with the blue suit.

The bunker was code named "Project Greek Island". It became defunct a while back when it became public knowledge. Presumably there is now some other secret bunker somewhere. Jim Justice bought the resort very recently and turned it partially into a casino. Though Forbes estimates his net worth as less than zero, that might be more of a moral judgement. item.title: Would anyone be interested in my turkey adventure and a sneaky fugitive?
item.description:
Made a brine that I never tried before with ginger root, but hole cloves, oranges and bay leaves.
I brined this 19lbs bad boy for 24 hours!
I woke up at 04:30 to get this on by 5. I then went back to bed. Thankfully, baby spice allowed me to sleep in and he didn’t wake up till close to 8!
Here it is after 4 hours. This was bad because in years past the Traeger wasn’t working well. I cleaned out the augur and fire pot over the summer and now it is more efficient.
I let it stay in a “keep warm” setting for close to an hour to prolong the cooking and got it down and then injected it one more time with butter and cooked the skin!
Just listen to the sizzle!
The best turkey I’ve ever made.
Yes, Felix got a bit of turkey too.
I placed the carcass in the garage refrigerator so I can make turkey dumpling soup. My dog would not leave me alone and made sure to get some of the drippings as I was trying to get it to the refrigerator.
